Introduction

Wang Fei Fei, known by the stage name Fei, is a Chinese actress and singer under Wang Feifei Studio. She is a former member of the now-disbanded South Korean girl group, miss A. In March 2010, the group began promoting in China. Later the group debuted in South Korea in July 2010 with the song 'Bad Girl, Good Girl' under JYP Entertainment. Their debut song earned them their first win the same year, as well as many awards at the Mnet Asian Music Awards (MAMA), Golden Disk Awards (GDA), and Seoul Music Awards (SMA).

In 2011, she debuted as an actress in the series 'Dream High', alongside fellow Miss A member, Bae Suzy.
In 2016, Fei debuted as a solo artist with the mini album 'Fantasy'.

In 2017, with the disbandment of Miss A, Fei moved back to China to continue her solo career. In 2017, she got her first proper role (she had only been making cameos in dramas) in the Chinese drama 'Swan'.

In 2018, with the expiration of her contract, Fei left JYP Entertainment and joined Huayi Brothers. She continued both her solo acting and singing career in China.
